Privacy Policy — Ashuzone

Last updated: October 2025

Ashuzone ("we," "our," or "us") provides an application ("App") that integrates with TikTok through the TikTok Developer APIs. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you use our App.

1. Information We Collect

TikTok Account Information: When you connect your TikTok account through OAuth, we may receive your TikTok user ID, username, and basic profile details.

Content Data: Videos and related metadata (title, description) that you choose to upload and publish through the App.

Usage Data: Technical logs, API requests, and error reports that help us improve the service.

We do not collect TikTok passwords or sensitive personal data.

2. How We Use Information

We use collected data to:

Authenticate you with TikTok through OAuth.

Upload and publish videos on your behalf.

Maintain and improve the App’s performance.

We do not sell, trade, or rent your information to third parties.

3. Data Sharing

Data is shared only with TikTok as required by the TikTok Developer APIs (e.g., when uploading or publishing content).

We do not share your information with any unauthorized third parties.

4. Data Storage & Security

OAuth tokens and access credentials are stored securely.

Reasonable technical and organizational measures are used to prevent unauthorized access or disclosure.

5. Your Rights

You may revoke our access to your TikTok account at any time in your TikTok settings.

You can contact us to request deletion of your stored data.

6. Children’s Privacy

The App is not intended for use by children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

7. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will always include a new “Last updated” date.

8. Contact Us

